    <briefdescription>
<para>RTOS wrapper for mutex / binary semaphore support. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para><simplesect kind="par"><title>Detailed Description </title><para>The sema class implements a C++ wrapper of the mutex API provided by the Zephyr operating system. See details in Zephyr <linebreak/>
 <ulink url="https://docs.zephyrproject.org/latest/kernel/services/synchronization/mutexes.html">mutex documentation</ulink> or in <ulink url="https://docs.zephyrproject.org/apidoc/latest/group__mutex__apis.html">API documentation</ulink>. The <ref refid="class_mutex" kindref="compound">Mutex</ref> class provides methods to wait for the availibility of the mutex and a method to signal the availibility. <dot>
 digraph Semaphore {
   rankdir=LR;
   subgraph {
     node [shape=point,label=&quot;&quot;,height=.04, fixedsize=true] ENTRY1;
     node [shape=circle, fontname=Helvetica, fontsize=10, height=1, fixedsize=true, label=&quot;Available&quot;] A;
     node [shape=circle, fontname=Helvetica, fontsize=10, height=1, fixedsize=true, label=&quot;Unavailable&quot;] U;
     node [shape=point,label=&quot;&quot;,height=.04, fixedsize=true] ENTRY2;
     
     ENTRY1 -&gt; A [ label=&quot;Initial value = 1&quot; ];
     A     -&gt; U [ label=&quot;Lock (value = 0)&quot; ];
     A     -&gt; U [ style=invis ];
     U     -&gt; A [ label=&quot;Unlock (value = 1)&quot; ];
     ENTRY2 -&gt; U [ label=&quot;Initial value = 0&quot; ];
     {rank = same; ENTRY2; U;}
   } 
 }
</dot>
 </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
